title: Misfit Science Theater
description: Flying saucers! Shink rays! Far off alien worlds! Mind-bending special effects!Join Misfit Improv on a voyage through space and time as we dub a science-fiction film. That’s right, we’re showing an old movie we’ve never seen before and making up the voices, sound effects, and storyline on the spot! Be prepared for high-stakes hijinks and hilarity complete with space lasers and forbidden planets. It’s sure to be the next cult classic.
location: Asheville Pizza & Brewing, 675 Merrimon Ave, 573 Fairview Rd, Asheville, NC

title: LGTBQ+ Improv Workshop
description: Join us for a FREE LGBTQ+ improv workshop! Thanks to the incredible support of Campaign for Southern Equality, this class is led by talented Misfit improvisers, Megan Piscitelle & Stevie Ramirez. If you want to make a donation, it will directly benefit Campaign for Southern Equality. This is your chance to connect, create, and laugh in a safe and welcoming space. Come play with us!
location: Campaign for Southern Equality, 20 Oak Street, Asheville, NC 28801 - Street parking is free starting at 6p, and there is a lot around the back of the building. The entrance is also around back. Ring the doorbell and we will come let you in! Feel free to message with questions., 573 Fairview Rd, Asheville, NC

title: Improv All Play - The Jam Jam
description: An improv jam is where all levels can improvise together for free! Names are drawn, improv is created, people have a blast!An improv jam is a chance for anyone to improvise, and it's free! If you want to play, you put your name in a bucket and, when we draw it out, you're up. If you are new or new-ish to improv, don't worry, we will help you.If you want to just watch, that's fine too! The 'Jam Jam' is held at The Dr Wesley Grant Southside Community Center, every 4th Thursday of the month . For more info about us, visit Instagram @misfitavl or our website at www.misfitavl.com
location: Dr. Wesley Grant Sr. Southside Community Center, 285 Livingston Street, Asheville, NC 28801, 573 Fairview Rd, Asheville, NC

title: Free Intro to Improv Class
description: Hey Asheville friends! Check out Misfit Improv & Acting School's free Intro to Improv class. It's a laid-back opportunity to tap into your creativity, share some laughs, and build confidence.No need to worry about performing, just come and give improv a shot. Feel free to invite your friends along for the party! Make sure and RSVP to secure your spot. For more info about us, visit Instagram @misfitavl or our website at www.misfitavl.com.*Heads up, there are stairs to get into the space.
location: Misfit Improv & Acting School, 573 Fairview Rd Unit 21A, Asheville, NC 28803, 573 Fairview Rd, Asheville, NC
